parameters: Clea: I have finished reporting to the guild leader.

Clea: I don't know what to talk about, even though we're
not parting ways in death or anything.

Thief Nora: I've been so worried...! Whenever I take my
eyes off you for a moment, Clea-san, it feels like you might
disappear.

Thief Nora: Let's continue from that time! It's a charm
that worked well before we fought the dragon!

Thief Nora: Relm-san is an amazing person, but she's also
just a normal person. Recklessness is not good!

Priestess Sophia: I was completely at the mercy of the
gluttonous Nora-chan. It was more than just troublesome,
hehe, it was fun and amusing...

Priestess Sophia: Please don't go back to being alone,
okay? Just like the world of books, this world is also
vast.

Mage Relm: Please drink wine in moderation, as if something
were to happen to your health, we wouldn't be able to meet
anymore...

Mage Relm: Clea-san, please take care of your own body too!
You, the clients, and all of us should be important!

Clea: I was also worried about Nora-san. To someone as weak
as me, Nora-san's strength seemed like bravado.

Clea: Sophia-san, please don't let the past crush you. We
met and will walk together because you are the future.

Clea: I am truly grateful to all of you. I have been able
to stay safe until today thanks to all of you.

Clea: Everyone is moving towards new dreams... that's
why... I tried to send you off with a smile...

Mage Relm: I won't be able to become an Archmage by the
next time we meet, but I will become an Advanced Sorceress,
so please celebrate for me!

Thief Nora: I will be active in the Emma Mercenary Corps! I
will do my best to assist the leaders!

Priestess Sophia: I will atone for the numerous sins I have
committed under the guidance of Eleo-chan.

Clea: The next time we meet will be at the award ceremony
hosted by King Rex. Let's gather at my house, just like last
time.

Clea: Though it's a temporary farewell... let's definitely
meet again in this place!
Clea: Take care until we meet again.

Clea (Our friends are each heading towards their own new
dreams)

Clea (It's the same as before... just like when we said
goodbye after avenging... )

Clea (Just like back then, I watched the backs of my friends
as they moved towards their new dreams, while I was in the
position of seeing them off.)
Clea: Um! Could you let me see you off?

Clea: I feel like there's something I can grasp through
seeing everyone off to where they should go.
Clea: It's selfish of me, but...

Priestess Sophia: Hehe, let's do that. If Clea-chan comes,
Eleo-chan will be happy too.

Thief Nora: If possible, let's meet with everyone who has
taken care of us!

Mage Relm: Yes, that's right. Let's go and properly express
our gratitude. It's also necessary for us as Archmages to
maintain our integrity!
Clea: Everyone... thank you very much.

Please note that once you choose a location, you cannot
return and meet with the comrades you fought alongside.

Clea: It's good to see that the people who took care of us
are doing well.

Mage Relm: I'm surprised to see that General Atu is still
alive. Maybe he's constantly emitting some special magic
power...

Thief Nora: It feels like a fun trip, doesn't it? Where
should we go next--

Clea: I will now send everyone off. I'm grateful for you
all putting up with my selfishness.
Priestess Sophia: We all felt the same way.

Priestess Sophia: Shall I be the first one to... send
everyone off?

Clea (The journey where you put up with my selfishness has
come to an end)

Clea (Everyone said they were going to spread their wings
towards new dreams)

Receptionist Piste: Welcome back, Clea-chan! Everyone has
gathered in the courtyard, can you come over?

\CL 【Receptionist Piste's After Story】Continuing her role as
the poster girl of the Adventurer's Guild, Piste worked as a
receptionist. Her thoughtful care healed the hearts of many
male members and led to misunderstandings.

\CL In her personal life, she married a deliveryman and was
blessed with three children.

\CL Piste was very popular not only within the guild but
also in the town, so her husband lived in fear of
retaliation until their children were born.
